data.content:
noun
plural ~ falls
[noncount] :the state or condition of falling through the air toward the ground
a parachutist in free fall [=a parachutist who is falling through the air before the parachute opens]
[noncount] :the condition of quickly becoming lower, less, or fewer
Sales were in free fall.
Stock prices have gone into free fall. [=they are going down very quickly]
[count] :a fast or continuing drop
There has been a free fall in stock prices. [=stock prices have gone down very quickly]
sự rơi tự do
